---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'top-picks', text: 'Our Top Picks', level: 2 },
  { id: 'leaving-poland', text: 'Leaving Polish Healthcare', level: 2 },
  { id: 'eu-mobility', text: 'EU Mobility', level: 2 },
  { id: 'comparison-table', text: 'Quick Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'detailed-reviews', text: 'Detailed Reviews', level: 2 },
  { id: 'popular-destinations', text: 'Popular Destinations', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Best Europe Insurance', href: '/best/europe-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best UK Expat Insurance', href: '/best/uk-expat-insurance' },
  { title: 'Best German Expat Insurance', href: '/best/german-expat-insurance' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'euNetwork', header: 'EU Network' },
  { key: 'ukNetwork', header: 'UK Network' },
  { key: 'polandCoverage', header: 'Poland Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Starting Price' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', euNetwork: 'Excellent', ukNetwork: 'Strong', polandCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'PLN 750/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', euNetwork: 'Excellent', ukNetwork: 'Good', polandCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'PLN 700/mo' },
  { provider: 'Bupa Global', euNetwork: 'Excellent', ukNetwork: 'Excellent', polandCoverage: 'Add-on', price: 'PLN 850/mo' },
  { provider: 'PZU', euNetwork: 'Limited', ukNetwork: 'Limited', polandCoverage: 'Included', price: 'PLN 450/mo' },
  { provider: 'Warta', euNetwork: 'Limited', ukNetwork: 'Limited', polandCoverage: 'Included', price: 'PLN 400/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Best Health Insurance for Polish Expats 2026"
  description="Compare international health insurance for Polish expats. Find coverage for the UK, Germany, Netherlands, and other EU destinations."
  headline="Best Insurance for Polish Expats in 2026"
  subheadline="Poles are one of Europe's most mobile populations. Here's how to stay covered in the UK, Germany, and across the EU while understanding your Polish healthcare rights."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/pages/polish-expat-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Cigna Quote →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="top-picks">Our Top Picks</h2>
  <p>
    Polish expats are found across Europe—especially in the UK, Germany, Netherlands, and Ireland. As EU citizens, Poles have healthcare rights throughout the EU, but understanding how these work is important. Here's what we recommend:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Best overall for Polish expats. Excellent EU and UK networks, comprehensive coverage.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Strong European coverage at competitive prices. Great EU networks.</li>
    <li><strong>Bupa Global:</strong> Premium option with excellent UK networks. Ideal for UK-based Poles.</li>
    <li><strong>PZU:</strong> Poland's largest insurer with some international products. Familiar brand, includes Poland.</li>
    <li><strong>Warta:</strong> Major Polish insurer with international options. Good for Poland-focused coverage.</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Post-Brexit UK Coverage"
    description="Brexit changed healthcare access for EU citizens in the UK. Polish nationals living in the UK need to understand their NHS rights based on immigration status. Private insurance supplements NHS and covers transitions."
    buttonText="Get UK Coverage Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="leaving-poland">Leaving Polish Healthcare</h2>
  <p>
    Poland has a public healthcare system (NFZ) funded through employment contributions. Here's what happens when you leave:
  </p>

  <h3>NFZ (National Health Fund)</h3>
  <p>
    Polish healthcare is provided through NFZ, funded by mandatory health insurance contributions (składka zdrowotna). When you work abroad and no longer contribute to NFZ, your Polish coverage lapses.
  </p>

  <h3>EKUZ (European Health Card)</h3>
  <p>
    The EKUZ card (European Health Insurance Card) provides emergency coverage in EU/EEA countries for Polish residents. It covers necessary treatment during temporary stays—not comprehensive coverage for living abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>EU Social Security Coordination</h3>
  <p>
    When working in another EU country, you typically join that country's healthcare system. S1 forms can maintain Polish healthcare responsibility in some cases (posted workers, pensioners, frontier workers).
  </p>

  <h3>Private Polish Insurance</h3>
  <p>
    Private insurers (PZU, Warta, Allianz Polska) offer products for Poles abroad. Coverage varies—international networks are typically limited compared to global insurers.
  </p>

  <h2 id="eu-mobility">EU Mobility</h2>
  <p>
    As EU citizens, Poles have specific healthcare rights:
  </p>

  <h3>Working in Another EU Country</h3>
  <p>
    When employed in another EU country, you generally access healthcare through that country's system. Your employer makes local contributions. You're covered by local social security.
  </p>

  <h3>Posted Workers</h3>
  <p>
    Poles posted abroad by Polish employers may remain in the Polish system via A1 certificate. Your Polish employer continues NFZ contributions. S1 forms enable healthcare access abroad.
  </p>

  <h3>Self-Employment</h3>
  <p>
    Self-employed Poles moving within the EU can choose which country's system applies, subject to rules. Many need private insurance during transitions or to enhance access.
  </p>

  <h3>UK After Brexit</h3>
  <p>
    Polish nationals in the UK under the EU Settlement Scheme have NHS access. New arrivals must qualify through work or residence. Understanding your status is critical for NHS access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Returning to Poland</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      When returning to Poland, you need to re-register for NFZ coverage. If employed, your employer handles this. If self-employed or unemployed, you need to arrange coverage—there may be waiting periods.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="comparison-table">Quick Comparison</h2>
  <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />

  <h2 id="detailed-reviews">Detailed Reviews</h2>

  <h3>Cigna Global</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global offers comprehensive international coverage with excellent EU and UK networks. Strong presence in key Polish expat destinations. Plans come in three tiers with coverage up to unlimited.
  </p>

  <p>
    24/7 service available. Poland coverage can be added for visits home.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Polish expats wanting reliable coverage across the EU and UK.
  </p>

  <h3>Allianz Care</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers excellent European coverage at competitive prices. Allianz has strong presence in Poland too. Good value for comprehensive EU coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Polish expats in EU countries seeking strong European networks at good value.
  </p>

  <h3>Bupa Global</h3>
  <p>
    Bupa Global offers premium international coverage with excellent UK networks. Ideal for Poles in the UK wanting faster access than NHS provides.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Polish expats in the UK who want premium coverage and faster access.
  </p>

  <h3>PZU</h3>
  <p>
    PZU is Poland's largest insurer and offers some international products. Familiar brand, Polish service, Poland coverage included automatically. International networks are limited compared to global specialists.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Polish expats who prefer familiar Polish service with integrated home coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Warta</h3>
  <p>
    Warta is a major Polish insurer offering international coverage options. Familiar service, Poland coverage included. Networks adequate for basic international needs.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Best for:</strong> Polish expats who want familiar service and primarily need Poland coverage.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare EU Coverage"
    description="As EU citizens, Poles have healthcare rights—but private insurance provides enhanced access, faster service, and coverage during transitions."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <h2 id="popular-destinations">Popular Destinations</h2>
  <p>
    Polish expats concentrate in specific countries:
  </p>

  <h3>United Kingdom</h3>
  <p>
    Largest Polish diaspora outside Poland—over 1 million Poles. Post-Brexit, NHS access depends on immigration status. EU Settlement Scheme holders have NHS access. Private insurance supplements NHS waiting times.
  </p>

  <h3>Germany</h3>
  <p>
    Significant Polish community, especially in western Germany. German statutory insurance (GKV) covers employees. Many Poles commute (frontier workers) with complex healthcare arrangements.
  </p>

  <h3>Netherlands</h3>
  <p>
    Growing Polish community. Dutch mandatory insurance (zorgverzekering) covers all residents. Employers must ensure workers have coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>Ireland</h3>
  <p>
    Large Polish community. Irish public healthcare access depends on residence. Many Polish workers have employer or private coverage.
  </p>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Can I use EKUZ for living abroad?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">EKUZ covers emergency/necessary treatment during temporary stays. Living and working abroad requires either host country coverage or international private insurance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What happens to NFZ when I leave?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">NFZ coverage lapses when you stop contributing (i.e., stop working in Poland). Working in another EU country transfers you to that country's system.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Do I have NHS access in the UK?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Polish nationals with EU Settlement Scheme status have NHS access. New arrivals must qualify through work or residence. Check your specific status.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What about coverage during Poland visits?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">PZU and Warta include Poland automatically. International insurers offer Poland as a coverage region. EKUZ from your host country covers emergencies.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">Is PZU or Cigna better?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">PZU offers Polish familiarity and includes Poland. Cigna has stronger global networks. Choose based on destination needs and how important Polish integration is.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg border border-neutral-200">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2">What if I'm a frontier worker?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600">Frontier workers (living in Poland, working abroad) have special rules. You may access healthcare in both countries. Arrangements depend on your specific situation.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Final Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Polish expats have EU healthcare rights, but private insurance provides enhanced access and covers transitions. <strong>Cigna Global</strong> and <strong>Allianz Care</strong> offer excellent EU coverage. <strong>Bupa Global</strong> is ideal for UK-based Poles wanting faster NHS alternatives.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>PZU</strong> and <strong>Warta</strong> suit those who prefer Polish service with included home coverage.
  </p>

  <p>
    Understand your EU rights, but recognize that private insurance provides superior access, faster service, and crucial coverage during employment transitions.
  </p>

</PageShell>
